# Install lifecycle scripts are disabled at the root on purpose.
#
# The vendored forks under v3/vendor/** are file:-linked optional dependencies
# whose paths are managed in package-lock.json. When a lifecycle script inside
# that optional subtree fails (agentic-flow's esbuild version check does), npm's
# reify step marks the subtree failed and PRUNES the managed path — deleting the
# vendored SOURCE directory from the working tree. ignore-scripts prevents the
# failure, so nothing is pruned. Explicit `npm run <script>` still works.
#
# Native modules that genuinely need a build step are rebuilt explicitly:
#   npm rebuild sharp
ignore-scripts=true
